This document lists any third-party code used by the Web Cache Exporter.
Each third-party library is contained in a subdirectory next to this
text file. This file documents why a library was used, who made it,
where it can be found, and any modifications that were made to it.

======================================================================
sha256
======================================================================

Used to generate SHA-256 hashes.

Author: LekKit
Page: https://github.com/LekKit/sha256
Version: c6cf8e5 (2022-12-08)
License: MIT

======================================================================
Zlib
======================================================================

Used to decompress files in the Gzip, Zlib, and raw DEFLATE formats.

Author: Jean-loup Gailly and Mark Adler
Page: https://zlib.net/
Version: 1.3 (2023-08-18)
License: Zlib

======================================================================
Brotli
======================================================================

Used to decompress files in the Brotli format.

Author: Google
Page: https://github.com/google/brotli
Version: 1.1.0 (2023-08-31)
License: MIT

======================================================================
msinttypes
======================================================================

Used to compile any third-party code that includes stdint.h and inttypes.h.

These headers were not included in Visual Studio 2005 which was the last
version to support Windows 9x.

Author: Alexander Chemeris
Page: https://code.google.com/archive/p/msinttypes/
Page: https://github.com/chemeris/msinttypes
Version: r29 (2013-05-24)
License: BSD-3-Clause
